metadata.name: Henoheno Samurai #2794
metadata.description:
This work was inspired by Otsu-e(大津絵), a Japanese painting in the Edo period. Otsu-e were inexpensive paintings made as souvenirs. Although mass-produced using paper stencils, the artisans painted by hand, resulting in variations in the quality of their work. Connoisseurs found them interesting and collected them as works of art. Otsu-e showed a new value of beauty in Japanese art, different from Ukiyo-e (浮世絵) which are prints, and from fine art paintings which are one-of-a-kind artworks.

This work is made of canvas2D Bezier curves. Not just a combination of parts, but also a random displacement of the Bezier curve points to lose the shape. This is intended to create fun with the Otsu-e-like effect.


Features:
This profile is made up of 8 parts (brows, eyes, nose, mouth, ear, contour, hair, and body). Each part has 100 basic types. 
There are 7 skin colors and 12 kimono colors. Each RGB value of the colors is randomly added within a range of ±10. In addition, there are 70 kimono patterns. 
The distortion rate due to displacement of Bezier curve points is 0.0~50.0. 


BTW The title "Henoheno" is taken from the Japanese character picture "Henohenomoheji" known since the Edo period.

metadata.name: El Churrito #381
metadata.description:
El Churrito was inspired by a coworker who used to talk all day about how he wanted to make a living selling churros.

Imagine yourself in the office earning the same as the employee next door and listening to him all day about the quality of his churros.

The day has come, meet El Churrito.

Features:
Body - 6 types
Top Hair - 16 types
Special - 2 types
Eye - 7 types
Mouth - 7 types
Eyebrow - 5 types
Filing - 44 types
Filing_1 – 2 types
Filing_2 - 3 types
Background - 5 groups


Project Twitter: @ElChurritoXTZ
Created by TRB and designed by ZEBRA
Code by @just_p01nt

metadata.name: Ma cité, la nuit. #1
metadata.description:
Se promener la nuit, regarder glisser la lumière.
Prendre des photos des réverbères.

On a parfois de bonnes surprises.


Lumière, matières, couleurs, variations.



==================================
-- Controls --

Use wheel or pinch to zoom out and see the full model.
Touch or drag to rotate.
Generate your own high quality screenshots.

-- Keyboard --

R: enable/disable autorotate
B: alternate through black, grey and unique color backgrounds
S: save 8k 16/9 picture (8192x4608)
P: save 8k panoramic picture (8192x2304)
C: save 8k square picture (8192x8192)

==================================

Made with ❤️️, science and threejs.
Donations included.

metadata.name: Sequentia #192
metadata.description:
GM/GA/GE, this is my first project using (fx)params! HERE WE GO!

"Sequentia" is an experiment in making a seamless tiles pattern using lines and strokes. 


Params
---------------------------------
Pallet: Pallet section from the top 100 pallets 0n ColourLovers.com 

Density: Affects the number of cells used to generate the pattern

Balance: Affects the number of strokes used on each path of the pattern

Balance Amount: A custom value used to determine the line stroke thickness. Set to 0 for the defaults.

Custom Pallet: Use your pallet with a list of hex values separated by commas. At least two are required to use a custom pallet.

Dust: Add some dust to the overall output. Set it to 0 to turn it off.

Scratches: Add some scratch texture to the overall output. Set it to 0 to turn it off.


Royalties Splits:
---------------------------------
50% Donation to minter


Dependencies:
---------------------------------
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes
@liamegan1/fxhash-helpers

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size (see features for dimensions)

metadata.name: Astral #46
metadata.description:
Press "q" to hide the stars.
Press "d" to display the stars.
Press "p" to pause.
Press "m" to resume.
Press "s" to save as PNG.

"Astral" invites viewers on a captivating journey through the cosmos. This immersive artwork showcases a celestial landscape filled with mesmerizing planets, shimmering stars, and enchanting auroras. The interplay of light and color creates a sense of otherworldly serenity, evoking a feeling of wonder and awe.

metadata.name: Florescentia #32
metadata.description:
Click Open then :
Press "s" to save a png
Press "p" to get a metal print of your Florescentia

Florescentia is a work that has gone through several stages. I started with a foundation, depicting a nebula in space with intricate details. As I let myself be guided by the code, I drew inspiration from artworks like "Meridian" by Matt DesLauries and "Anticyclone" by William Mapan. The freedom and fulfillment I experienced in the creative process inspired me to name it Florescentia.
